# Calibration for code-review-graph v2.3.2
#
# Augments DEFAULT_IGNORE_PATTERNS in incremental.py:34-71.
# Defaults already cover: node_modules, .venv, venv, __pycache__, *.pyc,
# dist, build, coverage, *.db, *.sqlite, *.lock, package-lock.json, etc.
#
# Matching is fnmatch-based (incremental.py:218), NOT full gitignore.
# Use `<dir>/**` for recursive directory exclusion.
# Negation (!pattern) and anchored paths (/foo) are NOT supported.
#
# File enumeration prefers `git ls-files` (incremental.py:384), so anything
# in .gitignore is already excluded. These patterns are defense-in-depth for
# tracked-but-noisy paths and binary research artifacts.

# Test/coverage artifacts not in defaults
.pytest_cache/**
htmlcov/**
.ruff_cache/**
.mypy_cache/**

# Research output (large, regenerated, not source)
reports/**
logs/**
output/**

# Binary data formats — would be tracked by git but are not parseable code
*.dbn
*.dbn.zst
*.parquet
*.csv
*.feather
*.arrow
*.pkl
*.pickle
*.npy
*.npz
*.h5
*.hdf5

# Generated/snapshot artifacts (per docs/governance/document_authority.md)
REPO_MAP.md
docs/context/**

# Tooling local state
.claude/hooks/.completion-notify-last
.gitnexus/**
